Data Foundations for Machine Learning
Practical Assignment Research Paper
Title: Student Daily Study Habits and Academic Performance Dataset
1. Dataset Topic and Collection Method

This dataset was designed to explore the relationship between students’ daily study habits, lifestyle behaviors, and academic performance.
The data was manually collected through a short survey questionnaire distributed to students within my class and nearby study groups.

The questionnaire gathered the following information:

Age and gender

Average daily study hours

Average sleep duration per night

Daily time spent on social media

Class attendance percentage

Most recent exam score (used as the prediction target)

A total of 60 student responses were collected over three days.
Because the responses were first written manually and later entered into a spreadsheet, the dataset naturally contains minor errors, missing values, and inconsistencies, reflecting real-world data collection challenges.

2. Features (X) and Label (y)

In Machine Learning:

Features (X) are the input variables used for prediction.

Label (y) is the output variable we aim to predict.

Input Features (X)

Age – Student age in years (numeric)

Gender – Male or Female (categorical)

Study_Hours_Per_Day – Average daily study time (numeric)

Sleep_Hours – Average sleep duration per night (numeric)

Social_Media_Hours – Daily time spent on social media (numeric)

Attendance_Percentage – Percentage of attended classes (numeric)

Output Label (y)

Exam_Score – Most recent exam result out of 100 (numeric)

Objective:
To predict students’ exam scores based on their study habits and lifestyle characteristics.

3. Dataset Structure

Total Samples (Rows): 60 students

Total Variables (Columns): 7

6 input features

1 output label

