4. Data Quality Issues

Since the dataset was collected from real student responses, several realistic data quality challenges appeared:

Missing values: Some students did not report sleep hours or social media usage.

Typing errors: Certain attendance values were written as words (e.g., “eighty”) instead of numbers.

Outliers: One response indicated 12 study hours per day, which may be unrealistic.

Class imbalance: More male students responded than female students.

Inconsistent formats: Some exam scores were written as “75/100” instead of 75.

These imperfections make the dataset suitable for practicing data cleaning, preprocessing, and validation in real Machine Learning workflows.

5. Possible Machine Learning Applications

This dataset supports several Machine Learning tasks:

5.1 Regression

Predicting the numerical exam score using:

Linear Regression

Decision Tree Regressor

Random Forest Regressor

5.2 Classification

Exam scores can be categorized into performance levels:

Fail: 0–49

Pass: 50–69

Good: 70–84

Excellent: 85–100

Applicable algorithms include:

Logistic Regression

K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

Decision Trees

5.3 Clustering

Students may be grouped based on behavioral similarity, such as:

High study time with low social media usage

Low sleep associated with low performance

Balanced lifestyle linked to high performance

K-Means clustering can reveal hidden behavioral patterns.

6. Conclusion

This project demonstrates the first critical stage of the Machine Learning pipeline: real-world data collection.
Unlike pre-existing datasets, this data was gathered directly from students, making it realistic, imperfect, and educationally valuable.

The dataset contains:

60 samples

7 variables

Missing values, inconsistencies, and outliers

It is well-suited for regression, classification, and clustering experiments.
Future steps will involve data cleaning, encoding, normalization, and model training, enabling meaningful prediction and analysis.

Overall, this assignment strengthens essential data science skills, including:

Data collection

Documentation

Data quality assessment

Preparation for Machine Learning modeling